OL,3,CWelsh Ambulance Service introduces
OL,4,Cchanges to how it responds to strokes
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government has announced
OL,7,Fchanges to how the Welsh Ambulance
OL,8,FService responds to 999 calls.
OL,10,FA new "orange" category has been
OL,11,Fintroduced in an attempt to improve
OL,12,Fcare and response times for patients
OL,13,Fwith strokes and other serious
OL,14,Fconditions.
OL,16,FCurrently, people suffering a stroke
OL,17,For STEMI - a type of heart attack -
OL,18,Fare grouped with many other cases in
OL,19,Fthe broad "amber" category, which
OL,20,Frepresents 70% of all 999 calls to the
OL,21,Fambulance service.
